PROJECT PROPOSAL/PSEUDOCODE
MBTIMATTER

PROBLEM STAMENT

Letting the students know their personality lets them identify their behavior, learning style, and habits. Yet, many students are oblivious when it comes to their personality. This leads to students doing incompatible study methods, having indecisive decision making, and inefficient role placement in groups. 

Most mbti tests require payment after the questionnaires are finished, some have a tiring amount of questions. Students need a quick but reliable personality assessor to quickly identify their most optimal roles in the community.

Objective 

Help students identify their personality type using the MBTI framework
Improve self-awareness and decision-making in academics
Encourage better teamwork by aligning roles with personality types
Provide instant, clear, and understandable results

Features 
Y/N type questions
Hasty Identification 

Inputs/output 
Input
Student decides to stay anonymous or not(skips 2)
Type name 
Answers Y/N questions
output
Students name(if not skipped)
Personality type
Short Description
Suggests study methods
Suggests role

